Fair Information Practices
The Fair Information Practices Principles form the backbone of privacy law and the concepts they include have played a significant role in the development of data protection laws around the globe. Understanding the Fair Information Practice Principles and how they should be implemented is critical to comply with the various privacy laws that protect personal information.
In order to be in line with Fair Information Practices we will take the following responsive action, should a data breach occur: We will notify the users via email
• Within 7 business days
We also agree to the Individual Redress Principle, which requires that individuals have a right to pursue legally enforceable rights against data collectors and processors who fail to adhere to the law. This principle requires not only that individuals have enforceable rights against data users, but also that individuals have recourse to courts or government agencies to investigate and/or prosecute non-compliance by data processors.
CAN SPAM Act
The CAN-SPAM Act is a law that sets the rules for commercial email, establishes requirements for commercial messages, gives recipients the right to have emails stopped from being sent to them, and spells out tough penalties for violations.
We collect your email address in order to:
• Send information, respond to inquiries, and/or other requests or questions.
• Process orders and to send information and updates pertaining to orders.
• Market to our mailing list or continue to send emails to our clients after the original transaction has occurred.
• Send promotional newsletters, charts, news and any related promotion to Music Worx.
To be in accordance with CANSPAM we agree to the following:
• NOT use false or misleading subjects or email addresses.
• Identify the message as an advertisement in some reasonable way.
• Honor opt-out/unsubscribe requests quickly.
• Allow users to unsubscribe by using the link at the bottom of each email.
If at any time you would like to unsubscribe from receiving future emails, you can email us at contact@music-worx.com
• Follow the instructions at the bottom of each email and we will promptly remove you from ALL correspondence.
Europen Data Protection Rights
If you reside in the EU the following provisions will apply to our use of your personal information, in addition to the general provisions of this Privacy Policy set above. We do not collect any sensitive data (defined under European Data Protection Law defined as GDPR).
Most commonly we will process your personal data where it is necessary:
• Purposes of pursuing our interests
• In order to comply legal obligations to which we are subject
• For the agreement we have entered into with you
• In order to take steps at your request for this agreement
We are processing your personal data to providing you with features, services, purchases, promotions, our marketing purposes and to investigate and prevent fraud.
Your rights are:
• Ask to delete your personal data and account
• Stop or start sending marketing messages
• Not be a subject of a automated processing based on your personal data
• Edity at any time your personal data on the website
• To rectificate your personal data, if you consider the information is inaccurate
Any request for a copy of your personal data must be in writing to support@music-worx.com. We respond on a reasonable period to your requests. We aim to ensure the personal data we hold about you is accurate at all times.
